    "text": "Section I: Periodic Health Examination\n4\nI.E Chronic Kidney Disease \nEarly kidney disease is usually asymptomatic. \nFigure 4: Algorithm for Chronic Kidney Disease Screening.\nDenotations\nABPM: Ambulatory Blood Pressure Monitoring, ACEI/ARB: Angiotensin Converting Enzyme Inhibitor/An­\ngiotensin Receptor Blocker, BMI: Body Mass Index, BP: Blood Pressure, DNA: Deoxyribonucleic Acid, ECG: \nElectrocardiography, eGFR: estimated Glomerular Filtration Rate, ESC/ESH: European Society of Cardiolo­\ngy/European Society of Hypertension, HBPM: Home Blood Pressure Monitoring, NCD: Non -Communicable \nDisease, PHE: Periodic Health Examination, SGLT2: Sodium-Glucose Co-Transporter-2.\nRescreen based on the risks\nTarget population\nRisk Factors:\n- High blood pressure\n- Diabetes\n- Cardiovascular diseases\n- Family history\n- HIV\nNo markers of risk\nDo not screen\nScreen \nTest:\n- Spot urine\n- Blood glucose\n- Blood pressure\n- Family history\nMeasure:\n- Kidney function \n    . Serum creatinine)\n    . Estimate the eGFR\n- Kidney injury\n    . Albuminuria/proteinuria\nDetermine if test results indicate CKD (eGFR \n<60ml/min/1.73m² or presence of albuminuria/\nproteinuria, ACR ≥30mg/g or 3mg/mmol) for 3 months\nYes\nNo\nLifestyles modification:\n- Smoking cessation\n- Balanced diet\n- Regular exercise\n- Limit salt intake to <2g/day\nMedical treatment:\n- Diabetes, BP and lipid \ncontrol (SGLT2, ACEI/ARB, \nstatins, metformin…)\nConsiderations:\n- Drug dosing\n- Use of contrast media\n- CKD complications (anemia, \n  hypeK+, bone disease, CVD,… )\n- Retesting\n- Follow up visits\n- Referral to nephrology when appropriate*",
