on about their substance use based on their risk assessment.\n• Responsibility: Patients take personal responsibility to change their behaviors. \n• Advice: Patients are advised in clear, respectful terms to decrease or abstain from substance use; encouraged to set goals to \n  decrease substance use and to identify specific steps to reach those goals. \n• Menu of options is discussed with the patient to achieve the desired goal.  \n• Empathic understanding of the patient’s situation is necessary. \n• Self-efficacy: Patients are encouraged to build on existing strengths to achieve desired goals.",
