    "text": "Section I: Periodic Health Examination\n12\nDietary Counseling\n4. Physical activity\nAerobic exercises improve cardio-respiratory and muscular fitness, bone health, reduce the risk of NCDs and \ndepression. Physical activity should be an integral part of excess weight therapy and weight maintenance. Ini­\ntially, moderate levels of physical activity for 30 to 45 minutes at a time and 3 to 5 days per week or 150min \n/week should be encouraged.\nDASH Eating plan\nThe benefits: Lowers blood pressure and LDL “Bad” cholesterol\nVegetables\nFatty meats\nSugar-sweetened\nbeverages\nFull-fat milk\nSweets\nSodium intake\nFruits\nWhole grains\nFat - free or low - fat dairy\nFish\nPoultry\nBeans\nNuts & seeds\nVegetable oils\nEat This\nLimit This",
