ble.\n- Early presentation if \nobstructed TAPVR \nwith severe respiratory \ndistress, marked \ncyanosis, and shock.\n- If unobstructed, Right \nHF symptoms and \nsigns, fixed split S2, \nSEM ULSB, \nhepatomegaly.\n- Treat as indicated in \nthe HF algorithm.\n- Surgical repair after \ndiagnosis and When \nthe patient is stable.\n- HLHS, Interrupted \naortic arch, complex \nCHD.\n- Variable-associated \ncardiac anomalies.\n- Symptoms depending \non the importance of \nthe pulmonary.\n- If in HF, treat as \nindicated in the HF \nalgorithm.\n- Pediatric cardiologist \nto decide the indication \nand timing of cardiac \nsurgery.",
