    "text": "Section Ii: Cardiology\n36\nII.B.2 Heart Failure\nHeart failure is a structural or functional cardiac disorder resulting from a ventricular dysfunction, volume, \nor pressure overload. Summarized below is the algorithm for the initial evaluation and management of heart \nfailure in children.  \nFigure 17: Algorithm for the initial evaluation and management of heart failure in children. \nDenotations\nALCAPA: Anomalous left coronary artery from the pulmonary artery; CHD: Congenital Heart Disease; RHD: \nRheumatic Heart Disease; SVT: Supraventricular Tachycardia\nReferences \n1. Kirk R, Dipchand AI, Rosenthal DN, et al. The International Society for Heart and Lung Transplantation \nGuidelines for the management of pediatric heart failure: Executive summary. Journal of Heart and Lung \nTransplantation. 2014;33(9):888-909. doi:10.1016/j.healun.2014.06.002\n2. MINISTRY OF HEALTH REPUBLIC OF RWANDA. RWANDA STANDARD TREATMENT GUIDELINES PEDIAT­\nRICS Volume 2.; 2022.\nHEART FAILURE\nConserved Ventricular \nFunction \nLeft/right ventricular \ndysfunction with a \nnormal heart anatomy\nCHD\nRHD\nCardiomyopathies\nMyocardial Infarction\nCor Pulmonale\nArrhythmogenic\nNon - cardiac causes .\nPresentation after 3 \nyears of age with \nhistory of bacterial \npharyngitis, migratory \narthritis , dyspnea on \nexertion, increased . \nprecordial activity, \nbulging chest, systolic\n/diastolic murmur , \nhepatomegaly , lower \nlimbs pitting edema\nPresentation during \ninfancy or childhood \nwith diaphoresis, poor \nweight gain, poor \nfeeding, tachypnea, \ntachycardia, central \ncyanosis, respiratory \ndistress, chest \nretraction, abnormal \nheart sounds, \nhepatomegaly ( most \ncommon in infants )\n- Dilated \n  cardiomyopathy \n- Hypertrophic \n  cardiomyopathy \n- Restrictive \n  cardiomyopathy \n- Myocarditis\n- Kawasaki Disease \n- ALCAPA\n- Chronic pulmonary \n  diseases : e.g., Cystic \n  fibrosis \n- Upper airway \n  diseases : e.g., \n  adenoid hypertrophy \n- Chest wall \n  deformities \n- Syndromes : e.g., \n  Down syndrome \n- Interstitial lung \n  disease .\n- SVT \n- Complete heart block. \n- Ventricular tachycardia\n- Sepsis \n- Renal failure\n- Do Echocardiography, \nEKG, Chest x-ray, FBC, \nRenal function, \nElectrolytes. \n- If asymptomatic, \nCaptopril 0.3-0.5 mg/kg/\ndose 8 hourly \n- If symptomatic with \nsigns of overload: \nLasix 1 3 mg/kg/day, \nAldactone 1-3mg/kg/day, \nCaptopril 0.3-0.5mg kg/\ndose 8 hourly\n- Do Echocardiography, \nEKG, Chest x-ray, FBC, \nRenal function, \nElectrolytes.",
