    "text": "- Arthralgia\n*Diagnosis:Initial ARF: 2 major OR 1 major \n  plus 2 minor\n*Diagnosis:Recurrent ARF: criteria for Initial \n  ARF OR 3 minor\n- Still prevalent in resource-limited settings\n- Sequela of untreated ARF\n- Definitive diagnosis made by\n  echocardiography\nMitral valve involvement \n      (most common):\nAortic valve involvement (comm-\nonly associated with a mitral valve):\nTricuspid valve involvement (less\ncommon, very rarely isolated)\n- Mitral regurgitation/ Mitral stenosis\n- The clinical presentation includes \ndyspnea, orthopnea, postural \nnocturnal dyspnea,systolic murmur \nat the apex, hepatomegaly, LL\nedema\n-Secondary prevention: Extencilline:\n© If ≤27 kg: 600,000 IU IM single\n    dose every 28 days\n© If >27 kg: 1.2M IU IM single dose\n    every 28 days\n- Treat as indicated in the HF \n  algorithm\n- Pediatric cardiologist to decide the\n  indication and timing of cardiac \n  surgery\n- Aortic regurgitation Aortic stenosis\nThe clinical presentation includes \nwide pulse pressure, syncope, thrill, \ndiastolic/systolic(AR/AS)murmur, \nhepatomegaly, LL edema\n-Secondary prevention: Extencilline:\n© If ≤27 kg: 600,000 IU IM single\ndose every 28 days\n© If >27 kg: 1.2M IU IM single\ndose every 28 days\n- Treat as indicated in the HF \n  algorithm\n- Pediatric cardiologist to decide the\n  indication and timing of cardiac \n  surgery\n- The clinical presentation includes \n  dyspnea, orthopnea, postural \n  nocturnal dyspnea,systolic murmur \n  LLSB, hepatomegaly, LL edema\n- Secondary prevention: Extencilline:\n© If ≤27 kg: 600,000 IU IM single\ndose every 28 days\n© If >27 kg: 1.2M IU IM single dose\nevery 28 days\n- Treat as indicated in the HF \n  algorithm\n- Pediatric cardiologist to decide the\n  indication and timing of cardiac \n  surgery\n                            Management\n+ Primary prevention: Penicillin V:\n   © If ≤27 kg: 250 mg 2 to 3 times daily for \n       10 days\n   © If >27 kg: 500 mg 2 to 3 times daily for \n       10 days\n+ Secondary prevention: Extencilline:\n© If≤27 kg: 600,000 IU IM single dose every \n    28 days\n© If>27 kg: 1.2M IU IM single dose every \n    28 days\n+ If allergic to Penicillins: azithromycin \n6 mg/kg/day, maximum dose 250 mg\nSupportive treatment:\nArthritis: >2 years old: Ibuprofen P.O 10 to \n20 mg/kg/day every\n12 hours (maximum daily dose: 1000mg)\nDenotations\nRHD: Rheumatic Heart Disease\nReferences\n1. Steer A, Gibofsky A, Sundel R, Sexton DJ, TePas E. Acute rheumatic fever: Clinical manifestations and \ndiagnosis. UpToDate.",
