    "id": 65,
    "text": "Glycemia: 90-180mg/dl \n(5-10mmol/L).\n• HbA1c <7% for most adult\n• HbA1c <6.5% for type 1 diabetes \n  without hypoglycemia\n• HbA1c <8% for people with frequent \n  hypoglycemia, limited life expectancy, \n  cardiovascular complications.\nClassification\nTreatment target \n2. Management of diabetes in outpatient\nFigure 21: Algorithm for management of diabetes in outpatient department.\nDo the test yearly\n1. First VISIT\nAssess Symptoms, \nrisk factors, physical\nexam, comorbidities \nand complications, raise \nsuspicion for diabetes.\nSigns and Symptoms\nPolyuria, polydipsia, weight loss, \nblurred vision, abdominal pain, \ntiredness, excessive hunger,\nRisk factors  \nAge >40 yo\nOverweight or obese\nFamily history of diabetes or CVD\nWomen with history of GDM\nHIV patient\nComorbidities and Complications\n• Hypertension\n• CVD (angina, MI,..)\n• Kidney\n• Eye\n• Neuropathy\n• If no history of Stroke\nDiagnostic criteria (WHO, IDF)\n• Using HbA1C,\n• Fasting Blood Glucose (FBG), \n• 2h OGTT (if applicable),\n• Random Blood Glucose (RBG)\nPrediabetes:\n• HbA1C:5.7-6.4%\n• FBG:100-125mg/dl\n(5.6-6.9mmol/l)\n• 2h OGTT:140-199 \nmg/dl \n(7.8-11.1mmol/l)\nLifestyle \nNon-pharmacological\n• Diet: low fat, low carbohydrates, \n  avoid sugar, sweets, juice, Fanta,\n• Physical Activity: 30min/d/5days\n• Smoking cessation \n• Diabetes education\nPharmacotherapy initiation:\nOral antidiabetic agents \nand /or insulinoltherapy\nType 1: \nInsulin therapy \n(See table Below)\nDANGER SIGNS\n• Dehydration\n• Abdominal pain with nausea/vomiting \n• Hypotension\n• Slow and deep breathing \n• Confusion\nDiabetes\n• HbA1C:>=6.5%\n• FBG:>=126mg/dl\n  (7.0mmol/l)\n• 2h OGTT:>=200\n  mg/dl (11.1mmol/l)\n• RBG: :>=200mg/dl \n  (11.1mmol/l)\nType 2: \nOral antidiabetic agents \nand /or insulinoltherapy\n(Follow next algorithm)\nDegree of Hyperglycemia and Plan\nBG (Blood glucose)>400mg/dl\nTransfer to District Hospital\nBG 200-400mg/dl with danger signs\nTransfer to District Hospital\nBG 200-400Mmg/dl without danger signs\nManage as OPD",
