ctor or nurse ever told you \n  that you have a problem with your \n  kidneys?\n- Proteinuria (Every 6 months)\n- Creatinine (Once a year)\n8. Screening for macro- vascular complications\nBrain (stroke or TIA)\nTransient Ischemic Attack (TIA)\n- Have you felt sudden weakness on one \n  side of your body that resolved immediately?\n- Have you had an episode where you \n  had difficulty finding words?\nHeart (Coronary Artery Disease)\n- Do you have chest pain that gets worse with or without exertion?",
