    "text": "Section Iii: Diabetes Mellitus\n44\nIII.B Inpatient Diabetes Management\n1. Inpatient Diabetes and Hyperglycemia Management guidelines\n1. Assess first:\n- Known diabetes vs newly \n  diagnosed diabetes\n- Determine type 1 or 2?\n- Hospital related hyperglycemia \n6. Mind: What is the “Correct” Glycemic Goal \n    In-Hospital?\n1. Low, high, and variable are all bad \n     • Generally, 140-180 mg/dL (7.8 –10 mmol/L)\n2. Higher if many co-morbidities or end-of-life\n3. Tighter if can do so safely: Acute stroke, \nAcute MI, Post-surgical, especially cardiac \n7. Goals of Inpatient Diabetes Management\n- Maintain MODERATE glycemic control\n- STRICTLY avoid hypoglycemia\n- OPTIMIZE long-term management \n2. Confirm outpatient \nmedication Prescription \n+compliance\n3. Assess control  \n Controlled? if HbA1c <7% or \nfasting and postprandial blood \nglucose below 130mg and \n180mg/dl respectively.\n4. Assessment of complications\n- Microvascular: retinopathy(eye), \n  nephropathy, neuropathy (foot exam) \n- Macrovascular:  coronary, cerebral, \n  and peripheral arterial disease\n- Comorbidities: HIV, Kidney dx, \n  liver dx, HTN. \n5. Assess Inpatient factors influencing glucose \n    control:\n1.Nausea/vomiting ->   intake\n2. Acute illness (e.g., infection)-> hyperglycemia\n3. Irregular access to food \n4. Special diet including Total Parental Nutrition\n5. New medications/doses (esp. steroids)\n6. Inconsistent medication administration\n7. NPO status\n8. Reduced activity levels\n9. Fluctuating renal/hepatic fx.\nNot Critically ill? \n8. Management approach  \nCritically ill but not in \n        DKA or HHS\nCritically ill? DKA or HHS \nManagement  principles: \n1.Try to continue preadmission \n  treatment Unless: \n- NPO or Decreased intake\n- HbA1C >8-10%\n- Frequent hypoglycemia\nManagement principles:\nHold non-insulin agents \nGive insulin:  subcutaneous or \nintravenous per insulin protocol \nConsider 50% of home basal\n insulin. \nManagement principles:\n Follow protocol DKA\nFollow the algorithm (below)\n9. Other considerations\nDischarge plan goal:\nOptizime outpatient  regimen \nDecide on discharge \nmedication 2-3 days before: \n- Oral agents only\n- Oral agents+basal insulin \n- Oral+basal-bolus insulin \n-  Insulin only \n>>>Check out patient protocol\nPre-op: monitoring \nGoal of glycemia: 140-180mg/dl \nPreviously on oral agents/diet\n- Hold oral agents if not eating\n- No basal insulin\n- No meal-time insulin\n- Corrective scale only\nPreviously on insulin\n- 1/2 – 2/3 usual basal insulin\n- No meal-time insulin\n- Corrective scale.\nCorrection insulin scale:\n• <150mg/dl: 0U\n• 150-199mg/dl: 2U\n• 200-249 mg/dl: 4U\n• 250-299: mg/dl: 6U\n• 300-349 mg/dl: 8U\n• ≥350: mg/dl: 10U",
