    "text": "Section Iii: Diabetes Mellitus\n48\nPrior pregnancy   \nDuring pregnancy\n   \nPostpartum\n• Optimize modifiable risk factors (eg. BMI, diet, physical activity).\n• Screening GLYCAEMIA in high-risk women\n• For preexisting DM:  Maintain HbA1c below 6% if and appropriate drugs: Insulin and metformin. \n• Screen for complications\n• Healthy diet, regular exercise >> unless there are obstetric contraindications.\n• Possible personalized gestational weight gain.\n• High-risk women:  detect early DM in pregnancy (if preconception positive screening)\n• Follow the protocol for all at 24 to 28 weeks gestation according to recommended screening and \n  diagnostic criteria.\n• Early postpartum OGTT to assess glucose status.\n• Regular long-term follow-up focused on diabetes and cardiovascular risk factor modification. \n• Family lifestyle support: optimizing diet, physical activity, and weight in the offspring.\n6. Preconception Plan  \n7. Screening and diagnosis\nFigure 24: Algorithm for screening and diagnosis of Gestational diabetes.\n8. Management of Gestational Diabetes\nFigure 25: Algorithm for management of Gestational diabetes.\nYes\nYes\nNo\nNo\n• GDM\n• 2h OGTT:  2 abnormal Values \n• Fasting >92mg/dl (5.1 mmol/l) \n• 1h >180mg (10mmol/l)\n• 2h >153 mg /dl (8.5 mmol/l) \n \nLifestyle medication (diet and exercise) +\nClose follow-up: Monitoring fasting and \n1 or 2 hours postprandial glucose for \n1 week or 2 weeks\nGlucose level values: \n• Fasting <95mg/dl (5.3 mmol/l) \n• 1hour postprandial <120mg/dl (7.8mmol/l)\n• 2 hours postprandial <153 mg/dl (6/7 mmol/l)  \nContinue lifestyle change and initiate pharmacotherapy.  \nLife style changes and glucose monitoring until delivery \nIs the patient willing and able to self-administer insulin?\nStart Metformin 500mg once a day with the evening meal.\nIf tolerated increase 500 mg with dinner and with \nbreakfast based on GLYCEMIA \nAn increase of 500mg to 1000mg per week is acceptable\n(maximum daily dose 2500mg divided into two doses) \nIf normoglycemia not\nachieved add insulin and \nadjust it until the goal \nachieved \nIf normoglycemia achieved \ncontinue metformin till \ndelivery \nInitiate insulin per protocol ( 0.7-1 IU/kg)\nYes\nNo\nFirst Antenatal Visit \nPresence of Risk Factors\nScreening with FPG, HbA1c, RBG, or OGTT   \nDiabetes depending on clinical decision  \nIF Abnormal \nManage as preexisting \nDiabetes\nIF Normal \nManage as GDM\nUniversal Screening again at 24-28 weeks for gestational \nDiabetes may be better if applicable (in case not screening \nor not diagnosed with DM or diabetes)\nPerform 75-gr 2H- OGTT, Diagnosis is made when \nFasting: 92mg/dl (5.1 mmol/l) \n1h: 180mg(10mmol/l)\n2 h: 153 mg /dl (8.5 mmol/l) \nNormal \nContinue routine care \nAbnormal Begin  \nblood sugar monitoring",
