    "text": "Section Iii: Diabetes Mellitus\n51\nCriteria for resolution\nTransition to long-acting insulin\nDKA:\n•\t\nBG < 200 mg/dL + 2 or more of: HCO3- ≥ 15 \nmEq/L or pH > 7.3 or anion gap ≤ 12mEq/L\n•\t\nNeg urine ketones if above not available (con­\nfirm repeat in 1-2 hrs)\nHHS:\n•\t\nBG <250-300 \nmg/dL\n•\t\nImproved men­\ntal status\n•\t\nEffective Os­\nmolality ≤ 315 \nmOsm/kg\nContinue continuous IV for 1-2 hrs after long acting started\n•\t\n0.4-0.6 u/kg for insulin naïve patients\n•\t\nNPH/Regular: based on inpatient DM protocol\n•\t\nHold regular insulin if patient is not eating\n•\t\nMay resume home regimen if previously on insulin \nAlternative Subcutaneous Insulin Protocol\nIf continuous infusion not available, for mild/moderate \nDKA:\n•\t\nInitial IV Bolus: 0.1 IU/kg given intravenously\n•\t\nMaintenance: 0.1 IU/kg subcutaneous q1-2 hr. \n(start immediately following bolus)\n•\t\nWhen BG <250 mg/dL, reduce dose by 50%\n•\t\nContinue until resolution of DKA or HHS, This regimen is not well validated and \nis modified from other protocols. Continuous IV is preferred as standard of care \nwhen available\nUseful Formulas\n•\t\nCalculated Anion Gap (>12 is elevated) [Na+] – \n[Cl- + HCO3-]\n•\t\nEffective Serum Osmolality: 2x[Na+] + glu­\ncose/18\n•\t\nCorrected Serum Sodium: [Na+] + 1.6x [glucose (mg/dL) -100]/100\n•\t\nFree Water Deficit: 0.6 x weight (kg) x[ (Na+/140) -1]\n• Treat underlying causes when identified or highly suspected.\n• Mental status is expected to improve with treatment if DKA or HHS are the primary cause, consider further \nevaluation if not improving.\n3. Management of DKA and HHS at peripheral health facilities",
