    "text": "• SOF+LDV can be used in patients with eGFR >30 ml/min.  \nIV.A.1.4 Complications Management\nApproach to anemia in CKD\nAnemia is defined as a Hb concentration <13.0g/dL for adult males and postmenopausal women, and an Hb< \n12 g/dL for premenopausal women. \nAnemia is a common complication of CKD due to repetitive blood sampling; blood loss and hemolysis; chronic \ninflammation; hyperparathyroidism and bone marrow fibrosis; shortened RBCs survival; Iron deficiency and \nrelative erythropoietin deficiency.\nFBC\nDiagnosis/Investigations\nAbsolute \nreticulocyte count\nFerritin level \nVitamin B12, folate\nTransferrin \nsaturation",
