    "text": "Section Iv: Nephrology\n65\nManagement of anemia in CKD                                                  \nBlood transfusion for the management of anemia in CKD\nBlood transfusion is rarely administered and must be avoided in anemia of CKD except in the following cir­\ncumstances: \n1. When rapid correction of anemia is required to stabilize the patient’s condition e.g. acute  Hemorrhage, \nunstable myocardial ischemia\n2. When rapid pre-operative Hb correction is required\n3. Symptomatic anemia with ESA resistance \n4. Symptomatic anemia in which the risks of ESA therapy may outweigh the benefits\nNB : Use leucocyte filter during transfusion if available to prevent rejection in potential transplant    candi­\ndates\nFigure 33: Algorithm for Iron Supplementation\nFigure 34: Algorithm for Erythropoiesis stimulating agents (ESA) therapy\nCKD  Patients: Hb target is set at  9.5 -11.5 g/dl\nNon dialysis CKD stage 3-5\nDialysis CKD Patients \nTSAT <20% \nSerum ferritin <200mcg/L\nSerum TSAT >40% and \nferritin >700mcg/L, \nwithold  iron suppleme-\nntation\nInitiate IV Iron and Target TSAT 30-40% \nand Ferritin 600-700mcg/L\nInitiate Oral Iron and \nTarget TSAT 30-40% and \nFerritin 600-700mcg/L\nSwitch to IV therapy if \nfailure to tolerate PO Iron \nor severe iron deficiency \nHb >11.5 g/dL \nOn ESA Therapy\nESA discontinued because \nHB over target \nNO\nYes \nNo ESA required \nHb 11.5-13 g/dL  \nHb>13 g/dL\nHb: 11.6-12.5 g/dl\nIf no prior dose reduction, \nreduce ESA dose. If dose \nreduced during last visit, \nmaintain current dose. \nGive ESA maintenance dose\nNo ESA \n1. Change  in Hb <1g/dl after 2 \n    months, restart ESA with \n    reduced dose.\n2. Change in  Hb >1g/dl from last \n    visit, hold ESA & monitor Hb \n    regularly",
