    "text": "Section Iv: Nephrology\n77\nTable 13. Summary of urinary protein interpretation \nNORMAL\nABNORMAL\nNEPROTIC RANGE \nURINE DIPSTICK\nNEGATIVE TRACE\n1+ or 2+\n3+  or 4+\nURINALYSIS\n< 0.3g/l\n0.3-3g/l\n>3g/l\nURINE PROTEIN CREATININE \nRATIO (UPC)\n<25mg/mmol\n25-200mg/mmol\n>200mg/mmol \n24 HOUR URINE PROTEIN RANGE \n<4mg/m2/hr,\n4-40mg/m2/hr\n40mg/m2/hr or 50mg/kg /day\n                \nNote\nIf the laboratory uses g/mmol as their screening units, normal urine UPC, = <0.02 g/mmol, abnormal: \n0.02 – 0.2 g/mmol, and nephrotic range >0.2 g/mmol\n4. Approach to management \nDefinition of Key Terms \n• Remission:  Urine albumin nil or trace (or proteinuria <4 mg/m2/h) for three consecutive days\n• Relapse: Urine albumin 3+ or 4+ (or proteinuria >40 mg/m2 /h) for three consecutive days, having been in remission previously\n• Frequent relapse: Two or more relapses during 6 months, or more than three relapses during any 12-month period\n• Glucocorticoid Steroid Dependence (SDNS): Persistent proteinuria (>2 g/g creatinine) despite high-dose prednisone therapy with 60 mg/m² (2 mg/kg) \n  daily for 4 weeks, in the absence of infection or nonadherence to medication  \n4.1. Management algorithm for first time nephrotic syndrome\nYes\nNo\nAge 3 -12 month, >12 years\nGross hematuria, complement\nactivation, persistent renal failure\nIntense daily prednisone a \ntherapy 60 mg/m² (-2 mg/kg)\nfor 4 weeks\nConsider Kidney biopsy \nRemission within 4 weeks\nConsolidation therapy\n(alternate day predinisone) \nfor 8 weeks \n• 40 mg/m² (-1.5mg/kg) Q48h\n  for 4 weeks, then\n•20 mg/m² (-0.75mg/kg) Q48h\n  for 4 weeks\nStop\nNo",
