    "text": "Section Vi: Pain Management And Palliative Care\n99\nCommon symptoms and management in the end of life care\nFigure 49: Algorithm for symptoms and its management in end of life care\nCommon and Specific Oral Problems at the end of life care\nNutrition and mouth care at the end of life care\n• Patients should eat and drink as they wish.\n• Educate Family that it is normal for patients \n  to lose their appetite, sense of thirst and stop \n  feeding towards the end of life.\n• Intravenous fluids at this stage will not prolong \n  life and will not prevent thirst.\n• Patients should not be fed if there is reduced \n  level of consciousness to prevent risk of aspiration.\n• Consider Holistic care.\n• Good regular mouth care is the best way \n   to keep the patient comfortable.\n• Maintain a moist mouth by sipping fluids \n  regularly throughout the day.\n• Brush teeth and clean tongue at least twice daily\n• Application of lip balm or Vaseline to dry cracked lips.\nHydration and Nutrition\nMouth care\nPain\n• Morphine 5 – 7.5 mg 4hrly(IV)\n• Morphine 2.5 – 5 mg 4hrly (SC)\n• Morphine 2.5-20mg 4hrly (Oral )\nNausea and Vomiting\n• Haloperidol 2.5mg od titrated to \n  bd (IV or SC)\nAnxiety or Agitation\n• Diazepam 5-10mg od titrated to \n  tds (IV)\n• Diazepam 5mg od titrated to \n  tds (SC)\nExcessive bronchial \nsecretions\n• Hyoscine butylbromide 20mg od \n  titrated to tds(SC)\n• Morphine dose will depend \n  on the patient, clinical picture \n  and previous history of opioid \n  use.\n• Anti-secretory medication \n  should be given when \n symptoms first occur and will \n be less helpful if given later\nSymptoms\nManagement\nSpecific Oral Problem\nCandidiasis\nPainful Mouth\nMucositis \n+/- Ulceration\nHerpes Simplex \nInfection\n• Ketoconazole 200mg \nod for 7 days OR \nFluconazole 200mg od\n for 7 days.\n• Nystatin 500000 IU 6 \nhourly.\n• Oral morphine 4hrly \n(for dose refer to pain \nmanagement guideline).\n• Patients should hold \nthe morphine in their \nmouth and use as a \nmouthwash for at least \n30 seconds before \nswallowing\n• Assess carefully for \nevidence of infection \nand treat appropriately.\n• Increase the frequency \nof mouth cleaning with \na saline solution, up to \nhourly in severe cases.\n• Oral Acyclovir 200mg, \n 5 times a day for 5-10 \n days depending on \n severity.\n• Treat lip ulcers with \n Acyclovir ointment: \n apply topically to lesions \n for 5-10 days.\n• For gingivitis or anaerobic lesions treat with metronidazole mouthwash ( mixing 50mls of IV metronidazole with 450mls of \n  water or Juice.\n• Educate patients to use this solution tds as a mouthwash for 1 minute before spitting out.\n• If mucositis is secondary to chemo/radiotherapy the dose of treatment may need reducing or in severe cases a break in \n  treatment may be advised to allow healing of the mucous membranes.",
