  },
  {
    "id": 171,
    "text": "12\nHF MIMICKERS \n \nRenal failure \n \nLiver failure \n \nLow serum albumin \ndue to malnutrition, \ncancer, TB, HIV, or \nother severe illness. \n1.2.1.1.4 Cardiac Output  \n Ask the following questions: \no Do you feel more forgetful? \no Are you lightheaded or dizzy, especially when changing positions \nfrom sitting to standing?  \no Are you peeing less? \n1.2.1.1.5 Co-Morbidities  \n1. Find out if the patient has any of the following co-\nmorbidities: \n HIV \n TB or a history of TB \n Pregnant or a history of pregnancy \n Diabetes \n Hypertension",
    "source": "IMB-NCDs-guideline",
