    "text": "39\n2.2.3\nPHYSICAL EXAM \nObserve the patient. Sometimes it is possible to determine severe \nside effects of hypertensive emergency simply by observation. Then \ncheck the following: \nEYES: Do \nfundoscopic exam if \npatient is \ncomplaining of \nblurry vision.\nBrain:\nSymmetrical \nstrength? Signs of \nconfusion \nHEART:\nTachycardia? \nMurmur? \nLUNGS: Listen for \ncrackles.\nLOWER \nEXTREMETIES:\nCheck for lower \nextremity \nedema.",
