    "id": 200,
    "text": "41\n2.2.5\nIMPRESSION \n2.2.5.1 Diagnosis \nIf the BP is between 140/80 – 160/89 mmHg (Stage1), you must ask \nthe patient to return for afollow-up visit before you candiagnose \nhypertension.  \nUse the following boxes to guide your decision: \nNOT \nHYPERTENSION\nBP< 140/90 \nmmHg\nStop \nhypertension \nworkup\nHYPERTENSION \nCONFIRMED IF\nBP> 160/100 \nmmHg\nGo to “Type of \nHypertension”\nHYPERTENSION \nCONFIRMED IF \nON 2 VISITS\nBP> 140/90\nBP< 159/99\nmmHg\nSchedule follow \nup visit or go to \nType of \nHypertension\n2.2.5.2 Type of Hypertension \nBased on the information gathered in the exam, decide whether the \npatient has. \nEssential or “Lone” Hypertension\nSecondary Hypertension\n2.2.5.3 Hypertension stage and danger sign \nTo know whether the patient should be transferred to the district \nhospital or started on treatment, choose the appropriate next step \nbelow by considering thehypertension stageand danger signs. \nIf patient has already been \ndiagnosed and treated for \nhypertension, skip to par 2.2.6",
