    "id": 208,
    "text": "49\n2.3 The Follow-up Patient Visit \nThis section emphasizes a systematic approach, which will \nhelpyou: 1. Confirm that the patient has hypertension; \n2.Assess medication adherence; and 3. Assess blood pressure \ncontrol. \n1. History (See2.2.1) \n2. Vital Signs (See2.2.2) \n3. Physical Exam (See 2.2.3) \n4. Lab Review (See 2.2.4) \n2.3.1\nIMPRESSION   \n2.3.1.1 Medication Adherence   \nEvaluate the patient’s ability to follow the treatment plan from last \nvisit. \n2.3.1.2 Blood Pressure Control \nReview the patient’s recorded blood pressure last visit. \nGood Control   \nBlood Pressure < 140/80 \nFair Control  \nBlood Pressure 140/90 – 159/99 \nPoor Control \nBlood Pressure >160/100 – 179/109 \n \n \nNO  TITRATION \nONE  TITRATION \nTWO  TITRATIONS \nUse the same \ninformation from the \ninitial visit for HISTORY, \nVITAL SIGNS, PHYSICAL \nEXAM and LAB REVIEW \nin the follow up visit.",
