  },
  {
    "id": 237,
    "text": "82\n \n4.3 Post-operative follow–up guidelines \nThe cardiac surgery post-operative follow up \no Should be done by trained Medical Doctors and Nurses in \nTeaching and District Hospitals \no Regular supervision by Cardiologists, National  Nurse \nCoordinator  and NCD Division/CVD Unit via    outreach program \nand communication  (RHD registry, cell phones, emails….). \no A web based national database should be developed for pre \nand post-operative  patients follow-up.  \no Required basic equipment and drugs: \no Laboratory equipment for INR or Portable INR machines & \nstrips  \no Warfarin (Coumadin) \no Heart Failure medication \no Echocardiography and ECG machine  \nFollow-up pathway \no Referral hospitals: Absolute review by cardiologist the first \nthree months, appointment are determined by cardiologist. \no District Hospital: By trained medical doctors and nurses and \nsupervised by cardiologists. \no Health centers: By trained nurses for secondary prophylaxis and \ndispensation of essential medications",
    "source": "IMB-NCDs-guideline",
