    "text": "112\n \n112 \n \nSummary table: Annex 1 \nCHECK LIST SYMTOMS \nAsthma \nseverity: \nDyspnea \nAbility to \nSpeak \nState of \nConsciousness \nRespiratory \nRate \nHeart Rate \nProtocol \nTreatment \nIntermittent \nWith \neffort \nIn \ncomplete \nsentences \nNormal \n20-25/min \n<100 \nOther causes \nshould be \nexcluded because \nasthma is over-\ndiagnosed at this \nstage \nSalbutamol Inh 2 puffs every 6 hrs PRN \nrsistent-Mild \nWhile \ntalking \nIn short \nsentences \nNormal or \nrestless \n25-30/min \n100-120 \nCall a physician \nand admit to the \nhospital! \nSalbutamol Inh 2 puffs every 6 hrs PRN, \nBeclamethasone 500mcg 1puff BD \nPersistent-\nModerate \nAll the \ntime \nWords \nRestless \n>30/min \n>120 \nCall a physician \nand admit to the \nhospital! \nSalbutamol Inh 2 puffs every 6 hrs, \nBeclamethasone 1000mcg 1puff BD \nPersistent-\nSevere \nAll the \ntime \nUnable to \nspeak \nDrowsy or \nconfused \n>30/min \nBradycardia \nCall a physician \nand admit to the \nhospital! \nSalbutamol Inh 2 puffs every 4 hr PRN, \nBeclamethasone 1500mcg 2 puff BD, \nAminophylline 100mg PO 3x/day \nsthma Attack \nAll the \ntime \nUnable to \nspeak \nDrowsy or \nconfused \n>30/min \nBradycardia \nCall a physician \nand admit to the \nhospital! \nPosition upright, give continuous albuterol \nnebulizer, high dose and prednisolone 60mg \nPO x 1. If symptoms uncontrolled after 30 \nminutes -> magnesium 2g IV x 1. Give \namoxicillin 500mg PO x 1 if pneumonia \nsuspected. Give furosemide 40mg IV x 1 if HF \nsuspected. Call physician and admit to the \nhospital",
