    "id": 289,
    "text": "138\n \nThird line \n  \nIn addition to lifestyle measures, adherence to medication and dose optimization. \nPreferred \nMetformine (if tolerated) + Basal (long acting) Insulin. \nAdd Prandial (short acting) with time if required* \n \n1. Start basal insulin 10 units morning OR bed time and Continue Metiformine\n*Bedtime insulin dosing if FBG is high(Pre breakfast) \n*Morning insulin if Blood glucose level high(Pre dinner).\n* If FBG is > 6mmol/l but < 8mmol/l for 3 consecutive days;No change\n*If FBG is 4-6 mmol/l on any day decrease insulin dose by 2 units\n* If FBG is <4 mmol/l on any day decrease insulin dose by 4 units.\nWhen:\nHow:\nGUIDE TO START AND ADJUST BASAL (LONG ACTING )INSULIN\n2.Titration:Adjust the basal insulin dose to achieve target(fix the Fasting first)\n*Monitor pre dinner BGL and FBG versus target\n* Increase by 2 units every 3 days until the glycemic control is achieved.\n3. Intensification:Once daily to twice daily basal insulin\n*If evening pre prandial BGL is high(180mg/dl)\n*After 3 months if HBA1c > target despite FBG and predinner BGL at target\n*Halve the current once daily  insulin dose and give the dose twice a day(pre breakfast and pre dinner)",
