    "id": 311,
    "text": "164\n \n7.2.5.3 Measuring creatinine clearance estimate using by cock \ncroft –gault equation \no Creatinine depends on age, weight and sex. \no In a patient with stable creatinine, we can use the following formula \nto estimate the creatinine clearance. \n \nInterpretation  \no ≥ 90 ml/min = Normal \no 60-89 ml/min = Mild Renal Failure \no 30-59 ml/min = Moderate Renal failure \no 15 - 29 ml/min = Severe  Renal Failure \no <15ml/min= End stage renal failure",
