  {
    "id": 315,
    "text": "168\n \n7.2.9 PLAN \n7.2.9.1 Initial management \nThe cause identification and early treatment conduct to success outcome \nare: \no Lower Blood Pressure; \no High BP is very common in CKD \no Keep blood pressure below 130/80 mmHg \no Treat proteinuria \no ACE-inhibitor should be used as agent of choice in patients with CKD \nstage 1, 2 and 3(creatinine<200mmol/l) and proteinuria. \no  Monitor potassium levelin  patients on ACE-inhibitors to avoid \nhyperkalemia.  \no Diet restriction \no Sodium(Na) intake should be restricted if high pressure or retaining \nfluid \no Potassium intake should be restricted if olguria or anuria(for example \nsweet banana). \nCHRONIC KIDNEY DISEASE 3 \nCHRONIC KIDNEY DISEASE4 AND 5 \nStart Iron supplements \nStart low dose of ACE-inhibitor if \ncreatinine<200 \nMonitor creatinine in 4 weeks and \nwhen indicated. \no Palliative care  \no Start Iron supplements \no Stop ACE-inhibitor \no Start Furosemide \no Monitor creatinine \no Monitor electrolytes include \npotassium,calcium \nlevel,phosphate.",
    "source": "IMB-NCDs-guideline",
